<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id60613f43-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58" identifier="/us/usc/t30/s1720"><num value="1720">§ 1720.</num><heading> Criminal penalties</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any person who commits an act for which a civil penalty is provided in <ref href="/us/usc/t30/s1719/d">section 1719(d) of this title</ref> shall, upon conviction, be punished by a fine of not more than $50,000, or by imprisonment for not more than 2 years, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id60613f44-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58">(<ref href="/us/pl/97/451/tI/s110">Pub. L. 97–451, title I, § 110</ref>, <date date="1983-01-12">Jan. 12, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/2455">96 Stat. 2455</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
